# ABS 3D printing BOM (India) — concise table

> All quantities assume a single-printer small workshop. Prices are ranges/estimates (Aug 2025) — final cost depends on brand, size, and seller.

### Essentials (required to print ABS reliably)

| Item                                                 | Qty | Why you need it                     | Example / note                                                                                                                   |                      Est. price (INR) |
| ---------------------------------------------------- | --: | ----------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------: |
| ABS filament, 1 kg spool (1.75 mm or 2.85 mm)        |  1+ | Main material                       | Many Indian sellers sell 1 kg spools; typical street price \~₹800–₹1,500/kg depending on brand & quality. ([tesseract3d.com][1]) |                       **₹900–₹1,500** |
| Enclosure for printer (insulate ambient temperature) |   1 | Prevents warping/delamination       | Off-the-shelf enclosures available; e.g., Creality-style enclosures. ([Amazon India][2])                                         | **₹6,000–₹25,000** (simple DIY <\$2k) |
| Heated bed (if not already fitted)                   |   1 | Needed to reduce warping            | Most printers include it; ensure 90–110 °C capability                                                                            |                       **₹500–₹3,500** |
| Filament dryer / dry box (or desiccant storage)      |   1 | Keeps ABS dry for consistent prints | Dedicated dryers (e.g., Creality Space Pi) or simple dry boxes. ([Cart2India][3])                                                |                    **₹1,500–₹12,000** |

### Consumables & adhesion

| Item                                             |                Qty | Why                                              | Example / note                                                |        Est. price |
| ------------------------------------------------ | -----------------: | ------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------: |
| PEI sheet / Build surface                        |                  1 | Better bed adhesion for ABS                      | Precut sheets for Ender/Prusa sizes. ([Amazon][4], [IARS][5]) |   **₹500–₹2,000** |
| Kapton tape / glue stick / ABS slurry            |           multiple | Adhesion aids; choose one                        | ABS slurry = ABS dissolved in acetone for strong adhesion     |     **₹100–₹800** |
| Support filament (HIPS for soluble ABS supports) | 1 spool (optional) | If complex geometries & soluble supports desired | HIPS soluble in limonene, pairs with ABS                      | **₹1,000–₹2,000** |

### Safety & storage

| Item                                                           |  Qty | Why                                                            | Example / note                                                                               |        Est. price |
| -------------------------------------------------------------- | ---: | -------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------: |
| Respirator with organic-vapor cartridges (or NIOSH-equivalent) |    1 | Protect from styrene fumes during ABS printing/post-processing | Reusable masks with cartridges available on Amazon/industrial suppliers. ([Amazon India][6]) | **₹1,200–₹6,000** |
| Silica gel desiccant packs & humidity indicator                | sets | Keep spools dry in airtight containers                         | Bulk packs or individual 2–10 g packs. ([Amazon India][7], [Dry & Dry][8])                   |   **₹200–₹2,000** |
| Nitrile gloves & eye protection                                | pack | Safety for acetone/sanding                                     | **₹200–₹800**                                                                                |                   |

### Nozzles, wear parts & spare hardware

| Item                                                       |     Qty | Why                                                                        | Example / note                                                                               |            Est. price |
| ---------------------------------------------------------- | ------: | -------------------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------: |
| Spare nozzles (brass) + hardened steel or stainless nozzle | several | Different diameters; hardened recommended for abrasive composite filaments | Nozzle prices range small — brass cheap; hardened costlier. Example vendor Robu. ([Robu][9]) | **₹40–₹1,500** (each) |
| PTFE Bowden tube / liner, PTFE couplers                    |   1 set | Replace when degraded                                                      | **₹200–₹800**                                                                                |                       |
| Spare thermistor / heater cartridge / bed springs          |   1 set | Prevent downtime                                                           | **₹200–₹1,500**                                                                              |                       |

### Tools & finishing

| Item                                                       |            Qty | Why                                 |                                            Est. price |
| ---------------------------------------------------------- | -------------: | ----------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------: |
| Digital calipers (0–150 mm)                                |              1 | Measure filament & printed parts    |                                       **₹800–₹2,000** |
| Flush cutters, deburring tool, craft knife, sanding papers |       assorted | For removing supports and finishing |                                       **₹200–₹1,200** |
| Heat gun                                                   |              1 | Local annealing/smoothing aid       |                                       **₹800–₹2,500** |
| Acetone (for smoothing, ABS slurry)                        | 1 small bottle | Post-processing & making ABS slurry | **₹200–₹900** (handle with PPE). ([Amazon India][10]) |

### Nice-to-have / upgrades (high ROI)

| Item                                                        | Qty | Why                                                |                                                  Est. price |                      |
| ----------------------------------------------------------- | --: | -------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------: | -------------------- |
| Glass plate (borosilicate)                                  |   1 | Flat bed surface for repeatable first layers       |                                             **₹500–₹1,500** |                      |
| BuildTak / PEI magnetic flexible plate                      |   1 | Easy part removal & consistent adhesion            |                                           **₹1,000–₹3,000** |                      |
| Filament spool scale or weigh-check                         |   1 | Avoid running out mid-print; check true net weight |                                             **₹200–₹1,500** |                      |
| Hardened nozzle (for carbon/glass filled filaments)         |   1 | Required for abrasive filaments                    |                                             **₹500–₹1,500** |                      |
| Filament recycler / extruder (for heavy in-house recycling) |   1 | Recycle failed prints/supports into fresh filament | Desktop recyclers exist; cost & quality vary. ([Amazon][4]) | **₹15,000–₹80,000+** |

---

# Quick shopping checklist (copy/paste)

* [ ] ABS filament, 1 kg (match diameter)
* [ ] Enclosure (or materials to make DIY box)
* [ ] Filament dryer or airtight box + silica gel packs
* [ ] PEI / glass build plate & adhesives (gluestick / ABS slurry)
* [ ] Spare nozzles (0.4 mm brass + 1 hardened nozzle)
* [ ] Respirator + cartridges, nitrile gloves, goggles
* [ ] Acetone (for smoothing & slurry) + heat gun
* [ ] Calipers, cutters, sandpaper, files
* [ ] Optional: filament recycler, filament dryer, spool scale

---

# Five short purchasing tips (actionable)

1. **Buy at least one backup spool** — filament weight variance and underfilled spools exist; keep a spare to avoid mid-print failures. (We cited typical prices and availability). ([tesseract3d.com][1])
2. **Invest in a dryer if you print ABS frequently** — prevents moisture-related print failures; dryers like the Creality Space Pi are widely available. ([Cart2India][3])
3. **Use a PEI or textured spring steel sheet over Kapton for reliable adhesion + easier removal.** ([Amazon][4], [IARS][5])
4. **Get at least one respirator with organic vapor cartridges** rather than a disposable dust mask — ABS releases odorous VOCs (styrene). ([Amazon India][6])
5. **Keep silica gel packs with spools and monitor humidity** — cheap insurance against brittle/noisy extrusion. ([Amazon India][7], [Dry & Dry][8])

